Back then the SoBW was selling for about 35-45kpp and LSoEE was 15-25kpp.  The large number of ppl I walked thru the quest via tells, MT'd for the turnin fights, and walked their group thru from start to finish, because someone didn't want to ruin all the time they had invested in a the quest may seem like a waste of time to you.  For them it was time invested in a quest that took anywhere from 3hrs (if you were lucky) to 2 months (if you weren't and didn't play much), but for me it was helping out someone.  Those players I walked thru, quested with, MT'd for, and told via tells didn't repay me with anything other than a simple thank you.  Yup, I can see how you perceive the selfishness of my actions.  Heaven forbid I wasn't off trying to get to 60 and get phat lewtz in Seb with your farm crew.  I play eq as I do AD&amp;D:  adventure, quest, and play eq as I want to play it.  Whether or not my actions are perceived as good or right by you is of little or no consequence to me.<br>
<br>
Yes, it must have been totally crass of me to MT for Dorriann and Skwar to get their TM shields from Valdanov, esp when I had formed the group to farm him.  Yup, giving up the chance to roll on a MQ non-no drop ash that could have easily made me a crapload of plat is totally selfish of me.  Again, I see the selfish angle of my pursuit of phat lewtz and phat plat.  Oh wait, I didn't get either or...odd.<br>
<br>
I guess when I lead all those UP raids after I had gotten a full suit of moktor armor from a group that used to farm UP before I lead the raids is a selfish act also.  Such a selfish act to have lead and MT'd those open pickup raids for over two months helping others.  Did FE members get drops during those open raids?  Yup.  Did Laberdere try to convince me to lie to some DE cleric (i think the cleric was shadowfinger) that had won a roll a Raldukan breastplate and tell him that he really won the Gantru Charm instead?  Yup.  I lost respect for Laberdere that day.  Especially after he later claimed NBG for a gantru charm and turned around to sell it in auction later that night.  Lab was totally a saint in your eyes, but you never were put in a position for him to tell you what truly happened that day.  You won't believe this, because it destroys the mystical vision of what you thought Lab was.  If your GL told you to lie or turned around claiming nbg to auction, then what would you have thought?  Respect him?  Admire him?  I left FE shortly afterwards.  Why did I lead those open pickup raids after I was already outfitted?  Due to Camieole and the others that grouped with her showing me kindness and I stated to them that I would help others as they had helped me.  Yup, totally crass and selfish of me.  For what's it worth...the reply you asked of me with the &quot;ROFLMFAO&quot; response you obviously strived to achieve.<br>
<br>
This is my last post on this thread...<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
Sir Maverickpoet Mistcallerbane<br>
65 Paladin of Tunare<br>
Proud member of Hawkestone<br>
